{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"96b0ca7cd30bb493310f134fed311141138b4461"},"timestamp":1501170196,"metadata":{"gitlab-base-url":"https://gitlab.com/","gitlab-id":"174","gitlab-project-id":"6581209","gitlab-url":"https://gitlab.com/langurmonkey/gaiasky/-/issues/174","origin":"gitlab"},"title":"Incorrect size of \"Sol\" via scripting interface","message":"*Created by: vga101*\n\nWhen querying the radius of objects with the scripting interface, I obtain the radius in km. However, for the sun the value is quite off (468156 km instead of ~ 696000 km). I guess stars are treated differently from planets (which have their sizes defined in the json files)...\n```\nfrom time import sleep\nfrom gaia.cu9.ari.gaiaorbit.script import EventScriptingInterface\ngs = EventScriptingInterface.instance()\ngs.disableInput()\ngs.cameraStop()\n\nname = \"Sol\"\nrad = gs.getObjectRadius(name)\ntext = \"%s has a radius of %f km.\" % (name, rad)\ngs.displayMessageObject(1, text, 0.5, 0.5, 1.0, 0.7, 0.0, 1.0, 38)\nsleep(3)\ngs.removeObject(1)\ngs.enableInput()\n```","files":null}]}